GHI Estimation using DLM

Data Pre-Processing

Lets clean the given data first, get rid of unnecessary hour values, were only interested in GHI values for hour 8-16.

df <- read.csv(file = './Bhadla new.csv')
temp = subset(df, Hour>7 & Hour<17)
ghi = temp[,c("Year","Month","Day","Hour","GHI","Clearsky.GHI")] # "Minute" not needed

Looks good, lets convert this into a time series object now. Conversion of this dataframe slice into an xts object will allow us to use the relevant functionalities.

require('xts')
traints <- xts(train$GHI, train$Date)
T = length(traints)
tail(traints) # Why does it still go till 2021 end?
##                       [,1]
## 2021-12-30 09:00:00 302.95
## 2021-12-30 10:00:00 443.11
## 2021-12-30 11:00:00 552.91
## 2021-12-30 12:00:00 567.34
## 2021-12-30 14:00:00 437.33
## 2021-12-30 15:00:00 283.26
plot(traints[1:T], main = "GHI", xlab = "Date", ylab = "GHI", major.format = "%d-%m-%Y %H")

First Attempt

Lets try to create a simple first order polynomial model.

library(dlm)
index  <- 1:T # FIXME:  Correct x-label

model = dlmModPoly(order=1, dV=1, dW=1, m0=600, C0=500) # + dlmModSeas(12)
results_filtered_dlm = dlmFilter(traints[1:T], model)
results_smoothed_dlm = dlmSmooth(results_filtered_dlm)

plot(index, traints[1:T], ylab = "GHI", 
     main = "GHI",
     type='l', xlab="Datapoint",lty=3)
# points(index,traints[1:T],pch=1)
lines(index,results_filtered_dlm$m[-1],col='red',lwd=2)
lines(index,results_smoothed_dlm$s[-1],col='blue',lwd=2)
legend('topright', legend=c("Filtered", "Smoothened"),
       col = c("red","blue"), lty=c(1,1))

FIXME: Now, to use this trained model to check for test data. (What metrics?)

testts <- xts(test$GHI, test$Date)
